Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.49,0:00:09.58,MiserableB,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(1,1545)}I'll send that miserable bastard to hell
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.00,0:00:15.46,Plan,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(1,1750)}I've come up with a plan so I won't get caught
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.99,0:00:24.37,Note,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(1,920)}Nichiuri TV Radio Division \N"Nino-chan's Until Noon Show" \NQuestions and Concerns Corner
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.88,0:00:23.52,DCMain,CULPRIT,0000,0000,0000,,Nothing will happen if this \Ndoesn't get picked up first.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.12,0:00:26.50,DCMain,CULPRIT,0000,0000,0000,,I hope they decide to use it.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.00,0:00:27.86,DCMain,CULPRIT,0000,0000,0000,,Just kidding.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.25,0:00:32.26,MiserableB,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,Challenging all cops and detectives
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.18,0:00:36.43,Plan,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,You'll never catch me!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.01,0:00:44.61,Plan,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(1,2500)}Now let me show you exactly what will happen
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.71,0:00:48.08,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Right now at this moment, \Nlight pierces the darkness!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.08,0:00:50.00,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Overcome all limits with \Nyour cool reasoning skills!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.00,0:00:51.76,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,It all begins with a letter \Nwith dancing characters!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.76,0:00:53.95,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,A suspicious contribution makes huge waves!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.95,0:00:55.46,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Always determining the one truth
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.46,0:00:57.14,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,with the body of a child \Nand the mind of an adult,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.14,0:00:59.49,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,his name is Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.01,0:02:47.02,DCEpTitle,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(401,1)}The Radio Questions and Concerns Show \N(Challenge Arc)
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.60,0:02:45.16,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,"The Radio Questions and \NConcerns Show, Challenge Arc!"
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.02,0:02:48.93,NichiuriTV,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,Nichiuri TV
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.75,0:02:52.02,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,I've visited Nichiuri TV several times,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.30,0:02:55.52,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,but this is the first invitation \NI've received from Nichiuri Radio.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.94,0:02:59.20,DCMain,MANDA,0000,0000,0000,,I'm Manda, the world's greatest producer.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.41,0:03:02.45,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,What? Th-The best in the world?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.74,0:03:06.21,Teruomi,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(250,460)}Manda Teruomi (40) \NNichiuri TV & Radio \NProduction Unit Producer
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.14,0:03:07.14,DCMain,MANDA,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Oh, please. I can't believe you \Ntook me seriously, Mori-chan.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.14,0:03:08.58,DCMain,MANDA,0000,0000,0000,,It's a joke.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.91,0:03:11.69,DCMain,MANDA,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}I'm actually only the second \Ngreatest in the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.21,0:03:12.08,DCItalic,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,What's with this guy?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.35,0:03:16.89,DCMain,MANDA,0000,0000,0000,,And this is the world's greatest \Ndirector, Kujirai-chan.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.88,0:03:20.35,Mamoru,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(250,460)}Kujirai Mamoru (35) \NNichiuri TV & Radio \NProduction Unit Director
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.19,0:03:20.59,DCMain,KUJIRAI,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}I'm Kujirai Mamoru. Nice to meet you.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.06,0:03:25.60,DCMain,MANDA,0000,0000,0000,,And beside him is the world's \Ngreatest writer, Yashiro-chan.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.04,0:03:30.48,DCMain,KAEDE,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}I'm broadcast writer Yashiro Kaede. \NI've been looking forward to today.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.14,0:03:29.61,Kaede,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(250,460)}Yashiro Kaede (32) \NBroadcast Writer
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.81,0:03:31.96,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Nice to meet you.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.96,0:03:36.73,DCMain,MANDA,0000,0000,0000,,Finally, there's Nichiuri TV's \Nposter-boy presenter, Nino-chan.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.16,0:03:41.24,DCMain,INUYAMA,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}I'm Inuyama Ninosuke.\NThank you for coming today.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.32,0:03:40.75,Ninosuke,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(250,460)}Inuyama Ninosuke (38) \NNichiuri TV Presenter
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.41,0:03:42.77,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,No, thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.77,0:03:45.71,DCMain,MANDA,0000,0000,0000,,So, Mori-chan, you got any \Nalcohol in your system?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.71,0:03:49.33,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Alcohol? No, of course not.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.33,0:03:50.86,DCMain,MANDA,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.86,0:03:53.53,DCMain,MANDA,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}World's greatest AD Abe-chan,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.04,0:03:56.51,Rie,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(250,460)}Abe Rie (24) \NNichiuri TV & Radio \NProduction Unit AD
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.53,0:03:57.13,DCMain,MANDA,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}ask him what he'd like to drink and \Nhave it delivered to his greenroom!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.13,0:03:57.78,DCMain,RIE,0000,0000,0000,,Got it.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.78,0:04:00.42,DCMain,KUJIRAI,0000,0000,0000,,Are you sure? We're about to start.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.42,0:04:02.76,DCMain,MANDA,0000,0000,0000,,What? But isn't it true?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.08,0:04:08.10,DCMain,KAEDE,0000,0000,0000,,They say Mori-san performs better \Nwhen he's had a drink or two.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.11,0:04:13.89,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,I suppose they're not wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.07,0:04:15.77,DCMain,MANDA,0000,0000,0000,,Then it's decided.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.96,0:04:19.18,DCMain,MANDA,0000,0000,0000,,Mori-chan, we'll be heading \Ninto the studio now.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.18,0:04:21.60,DCMain,MANDA,0000,0000,0000,,We'll see you later.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.60,0:04:22.78,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.05,0:04:28.84,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Is that Manda guy always like that?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.84,0:04:30.61,DCMain,RIE,0000,0000,0000,,I guess so.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.61,0:04:31.66,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.23,0:04:34.53,DCMain,RIE,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, what would you like to drink?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.82,0:04:45.05,DCMain,INUYAMA,0000,0000,0000,,Today's concern comes from TM-san of Tokyo.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.73,0:04:47.95,DCMain,INUYAMA,0000,0000,0000,,"I don't know what to \Ndo about the crazy woman
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.95,0:04:50.06,DCMain,INUYAMA,0000,0000,0000,,living in the apartment \Ndirectly above mine."
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.56,0:04:55.56,DCMain,INUYAMA,0000,0000,0000,,"She's noisy, and she throws cigarette \Nbutts and empty cans onto my balcony."
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.56,0:04:58.69,DCMain,INUYAMA,0000,0000,0000,,"I have no idea what to do."
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.98,0:05:02.50,DCMain,INUYAMA,0000,0000,0000,,I see. This is a truly pressing concern.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.91,0:05:07.20,DCMain,INUYAMA,0000,0000,0000,,Today's guest Mori-san, what advice \Ndo you have as a detective?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.63,0:05:11.08,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,It makes you angry because \Nyou think of her as human.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.08,0:05:14.41,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,That obnoxious woman is \Nnothing more than trash!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.58,0:05:15.53,DCMain,INUYAMA,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.69,0:05:21.99,DCMain,INUYAMA,0000,0000,0000,,I-I don't think it's right to \Ntreat people like garbage...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.99,0:05:25.30,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,TM-san, you should give her \Na taste of her own medicine!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.67,0:05:28.22,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Throw trash back onto her balcony!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.61,0:05:30.83,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Burnable trash, non-burnable trash!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.83,0:05:33.85,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Even your food scraps!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.06,0:05:36.44,DCMain,MANDA,0000,0000,0000,,Mori-chan's the best.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.44,0:05:39.07,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}No, food scraps aren't enough!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.78,0:05:40.11,DCMain,KUJIRAI,0000,0000,0000,,I told you this would happen! \NWhat are we supposed to do now?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.11,0:05:41.86,DCNote,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,Mori-san, you're the best!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.11,0:05:41.86,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Throw your extra large trash!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.16,0:05:43.00,DCMain,KUJIRAI,0000,0000,0000,,Play the jingle!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.52,0:05:45.09,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Show some backbone!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.61,0:05:44.53,Jingle,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,Jingle
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.56,0:05:47.03,DCMain,MANDA,0000,0000,0000,,He's still going!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.56,0:05:49.03,DCMain,MUSIC,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Nino-chan's {\i1}Until Noon Show{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.03,0:05:49.03,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,If you don't get her back, then \Nyou'll be on the losing side!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.24,0:05:54.83,Comments,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,Detective Mori's comments \NTruly nice
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.20,0:05:59.46,DCNote,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}The curtains are now rising on my plan
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.08,0:06:04.06,SeveralHours,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(670,670)}Several Hours Later
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.80,0:06:04.30,DCMain,KUMI,0000,0000,0000,,Answer the door, you harlot!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.12,0:06:07.03,DCMain,TOWAKO,0000,0000,0000,,What's all this about?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.03,0:06:08.80,DCMain,KUMI,0000,0000,0000,,I could ask you the same thing!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.14,0:06:10.98,DCMain,KUMI,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}You're the one who picked a fight with me!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.26,0:06:12.73,Kumi,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(250,460)}Kijima Kumi (38) \NHousewife
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.98,0:06:13.22,DCMain,KUMI,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}You trash talked me on the radio!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.48,0:06:16.34,DCMain,TOWAKO,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}What? I don't know what you're talking about.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.51,0:06:16.99,Towako,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(250,460)}Manda Towako (31) \NHousewife
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.34,0:06:17.98,DCMain,TOWAKO,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}It must've been someone else.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.98,0:06:19.83,DCMain,KUMI,0000,0000,0000,,Don't play dumb!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.83,0:06:21.11,DCMain,TOWAKO,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, stop!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.81,0:06:23.60,DCMain,KUMI,0000,0000,0000,,I can't believe you used the radio!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.60,0:06:25.05,DCMain,TOWAKO,0000,0000,0000,,That hurts!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.05,0:06:27.57,DCItalic,CULPRIT,0000,0000,0000,,They don't even know \Nthey're being manipulated.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.89,0:06:30.44,DCItalic,CULPRIT,0000,0000,0000,,It's all going exactly according to plan.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.57,0:06:35.31,DCMain,KUMI,0000,0000,0000,,You'll pay for this! Don't \Nthink you'll get way with it!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.31,0:06:38.50,DCMain,TOWAKO,0000,0000,0000,,Move out of here already, you nuisance!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.97,0:06:50.26,DCNote,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,Mori Detective Agency
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.20,0:06:49.74,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, Inspector.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.48,0:06:55.14,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,I did appear on a radio show \Nyesterday. What about it?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.14,0:06:58.37,DCMain,KUMI,0000,0000,0000,,I told you, I've got nothing to do with it!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.37,0:07:01.02,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Just come to Nichiuri TV.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.34,0:07:02.92,DCItalic,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,You're a witness.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.92,0:07:06.02,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,A witness? Witness to what?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.02,0:07:07.90,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,A murder!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.94,0:07:10.90,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,A-A murder?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.50,0:07:13.64,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Hurry.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.71,0:07:26.67,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,The victim is Manda Towako-san,\Nthirty-one years old,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.67,0:07:32.06,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,a resident of a nearby apartment building.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.06,0:07:35.05,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,She was killed late last night around 12 AM.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.54,0:07:38.28,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,She must've been struck with this metal pipe.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.28,0:07:38.93,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Ow!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.44,0:07:42.20,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,We didn't find any \Nfingerprints on the weapon,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.20,0:07:44.81,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,and there wasn't any \Nblood at the crime scene.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.26,0:07:46.49,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.49,0:07:49.19,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,So, why am I a witness?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.52,0:07:51.26,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Because the murderer's motive
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.26,0:07:54.70,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,may have had something to do with \Nthe radio show you appeared on.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.99,0:07:58.70,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,What? How is that radio show the motive?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.02,0:08:03.40,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Yesterday evening, the \Nvictim and Kijima Kumi-san,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.40,0:08:07.71,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,who lives above her, argued about the show.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.95,0:08:11.22,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,The listener's concern was \Nabout the obnoxious behavior
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.22,0:08:15.58,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,of the woman who lived above her.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.58,0:08:18.73,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,I believe the listener's name was TM-san...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.84,0:08:20.84,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,TM?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.84,0:08:25.00,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Those are the same initials as \Nthe victim Manda Towako-san's.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.67,0:08:28.65,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,I see. Then the obnoxious woman must be...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.99,0:08:31.90,DCMain,KUMI,0000,0000,0000,,Of course I'm angry!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.44,0:08:37.16,DCMain,KUMI,0000,0000,0000,,When I came home from work yesterday, \NI found a note in my mailbox...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.16,0:08:39.16,Nuisance,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,Nuisance
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.80,0:08:40.32,DCMain,KUMI,0000,0000,0000,,and a recording of the radio show.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.87,0:08:40.66,Nuisance,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,Now the whole world's laughing at you.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.02,0:08:45.92,DCItalic,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,It makes you angry because \Nyou think of her as human.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.15,0:08:49.60,DCItalic,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,That obnoxious woman is \Nnothing more than trash!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.90,0:08:52.92,DCMain,KUMI,0000,0000,0000,,So I went to yell at her!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.24,0:08:55.91,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Mister, you said those cruel things?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.91,0:08:58.14,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Well, you know...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.82,0:09:04.49,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,I have no excuse.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.49,0:09:07.96,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,I had a little too much of \Nthe drink I was offered.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.96,0:09:09.53,DCMain,RIE,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.82,0:09:13.47,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,No, no, no, no. It's not your fault.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.75,0:09:20.06,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, the building manager intervened
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.06,0:09:22.08,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,and was able to calm things down.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.31,0:09:25.98,DCItalic,KUMI,0000,0000,0000,,You'll pay for this! Don't \Nthink you'll get way with it!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.98,0:09:29.33,DCItalic,TOWAKO,0000,0000,0000,,Move out of here already, you nuisance!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.83,0:09:30.77,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.77,0:09:34.59,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Then you did invite the victim \Nout later that night...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.59,0:09:36.91,DCMain,KUMI,0000,0000,0000,,I told you, I didn't do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.91,0:09:38.27,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Now, now.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.01,0:09:44.32,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,But immediately after the victim \Nwrote in about her concern...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.32,0:09:48.02,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,It's not that simple, Mori-kun.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.76,0:09:49.61,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Yashiro-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.04,0:09:50.89,DCMain,KAEDE,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.30,0:09:57.11,DCMain,KAEDE,0000,0000,0000,,The listener TM-san isn't \Nthe victim Manda Towako-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.44,0:09:58.36,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.36,0:10:02.37,DCNote,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,Morikawa Tsugumi
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.82,0:10:02.37,DCMain,KAEDE,0000,0000,0000,,It's someone completely different \Nnamed Morikawa Tsugumi-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.64,0:10:08.42,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,But you received a CD recording of \Nthe show in your mailbox, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.57,0:10:10.79,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,That's it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.19,0:10:14.83,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Manda Towako-san, who happened \Nto share the same concern,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.83,0:10:19.64,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,heard the show on the radio \Nand recorded it onto a CD.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.20,0:10:23.64,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,She put it in Kijima-san's \Nmailbox out of spite.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.48,0:10:28.89,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,When Kijima-san heard it, \Nshe thought it was about her.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.21,0:10:30.62,DCMain,KUMI,0000,0000,0000,,I told you...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.62,0:10:32.06,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,But, Mori-kun,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.06,0:10:36.32,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,it wasn't the victim who \Nput the CD in her mailbox.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.55,0:10:37.44,DCMain,BOTH,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.17,0:10:42.63,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,I'm having Takagi look into it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.16,0:10:49.12,DCMain,INUYAMA,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't this case a little \Ntoo convenient for someone?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.12,0:10:52.13,DCMain,INUYAMA,0000,0000,0000,,It may be a coincidence, \Nbut the victim is the victim.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.27,0:10:54.69,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.69,0:10:56.71,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,We learned this when we arrived,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.71,0:11:01.76,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,but the victim Manda Towako-san \Nis the wife of Producer Manda.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.48,0:11:03.73,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,They're currently separated.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.73,0:11:04.76,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Your wife?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.96,0:11:08.44,DCMain,MANDA,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, but don't worry about it, Mori-chan.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.44,0:11:11.80,DCMain,MANDA,0000,0000,0000,,I was going to divorce that thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.60,0:11:17.12,DCMain,INUYAMA,0000,0000,0000,,But your wife was firmly \Nagainst divorce, wasn't she?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.62,0:11:19.50,DCMain,KAEDE,0000,0000,0000,,What does that have to do with this case?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.50,0:11:24.78,DCMain,KUJIRAI,0000,0000,0000,,But since your wife is gone, that \Nmeans your wish came true, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.00,0:11:29.75,DCMain,MANDA,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, please. Don't say such strange \Nthings, Kujirai-chan and Nino-chan.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.01,0:11:33.23,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,The conversation's gone \Nin a strange direction.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.23,0:11:36.91,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. It sounds like he's grateful \Nfor what the culprit did.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.91,0:11:38.76,DCMain,KUMI,0000,0000,0000,,I told you, it wasn't me!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.25,0:11:42.14,DCMain,KUMI,0000,0000,0000,,I did harass her a little.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.14,0:11:44.89,DCMain,KUMI,0000,0000,0000,,She kept boasting about \Nbeing a rising talent.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.99,0:11:48.77,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,She was a rising talent?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.33,0:11:54.24,DCMain,KAEDE,0000,0000,0000,,It seems that way, but that has \Nnothing to do with this case.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.24,0:11:58.82,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, but if the divorce proceedings \Nweren't going well...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.07,0:12:01.72,DCMain,MANDA,0000,0000,0000,,Mori-san, you, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.72,0:12:07.83,DCMain,MANDA,0000,0000,0000,,You're making it sound like I'm somehow \Ninvolved in her murder. Right?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.70,0:12:11.34,DCMain,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, please.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.97,0:12:12.33,DCMain,RIE,0000,0000,0000,,Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.59,0:12:14.33,DCMain,RIE,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.06,0:12:18.34,DCMain,RIE,0000,0000,0000,,I see. Right away.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.90,0:12:22.63,DCMain,RIE,0000,0000,0000,,There's a meeting scheduled in this room.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.98,0:12:25.64,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Understood. We'll move.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.59,0:12:32.57,DCMain,RIE,0000,0000,0000,,Inspector, there's a job I have to check on.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.41,0:12:34.88,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,That should be fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.88,0:12:36.10,DCMain,RIE,0000,0000,0000,,Excuse me.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.10,0:12:37.15,DCMain,KUJIRAI,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks for doing this.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.60,0:12:38.65,DCMain,RIE,0000,0000,0000,,Sure thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.52,0:12:42.44,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Inspector Megure.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.81,0:12:44.43,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,How did it go, Takagi?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.70,0:12:47.19,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, sir. About that...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.66,0:12:50.43,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,I knew it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.43,0:12:53.75,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Manda-san, this is the CD \Nwe were just discussing.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.29,0:12:58.71,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,You're the one who put this in \NKijima-san's mailbox, weren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.03,0:12:59.71,DCMain,ALL,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.30,0:13:09.51,Plan,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(1,1765)}Just as planned
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.94,0:13:21.44,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Our investigation revealed that \Nthis CD wasn't a recording
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.67,0:13:25.70,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,of the broadcast but copied \Ndirectly from the source.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.96,0:13:29.43,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Some of the station staff claim \Nthat yesterday afternoon
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.43,0:13:34.58,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Manda-san asked them to create a copy.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.95,0:13:38.08,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Naturally, he told them not to tell anyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.76,0:13:40.09,DCMain,MANDA,0000,0000,0000,,I wonder why.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.33,0:13:44.71,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Then you disappeared from the \Nstation for about two hours.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.89,0:13:47.07,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,During that time,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.07,0:13:51.47,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,are you sure you didn't go to the apartment \Nand put the CD in Kijima-san's mailbox?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.25,0:13:54.85,DCMain,MANDA,0000,0000,0000,,It certainly seems that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.04,0:13:56.60,DCMain,KUMI,0000,0000,0000,,I knew it was you!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.59,0:13:58.98,DCMain,KAEDE,0000,0000,0000,,Manda-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.21,0:14:03.36,DCMain,MANDA,0000,0000,0000,,During the review meeting \Nafter yesterday's broadcast
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.64,0:14:06.85,DCMain,MANDA,0000,0000,0000,,someone said they wish
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.85,0:14:11.03,DCMain,MANDA,0000,0000,0000,,the woman living above my wife \Ncould've heard today's show.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.57,0:14:16.75,DCMain,MANDA,0000,0000,0000,,I'd told everyone that she was frustrated \Nwith the obnoxious woman living above her.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.75,0:14:19.99,DCMain,MANDA,0000,0000,0000,,That's when I realized something \Ninteresting might happen
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.99,0:14:24.61,DCMain,MANDA,0000,0000,0000,,if I made it seem like \Nshe'd complained about her.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.12,0:14:31.26,DCMain,MANDA,0000,0000,0000,,You've gotta strike when the iron's hot.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.01,0:14:36.02,Laughing,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,Now the whole world's laughing at you.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.95,0:14:42.83,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,And just as you planned, \Nyour wife was killed.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.83,0:14:43.65,DCMain,MANDA,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.87,0:14:47.03,DCMain,INUYAMA,0000,0000,0000,,That's how he made someone \Nelse do the killing.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.32,0:14:50.03,DCMain,KUJIRAI,0000,0000,0000,,Manipulating another so he \Nwouldn't get his own hands dirty!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.03,0:14:54.83,DCMain,MANDA,0000,0000,0000,,No! I just wanted her to suffer a little.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.83,0:14:57.16,DCMain,MANDA,0000,0000,0000,,I never thought she'd be killed for it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.16,0:15:01.79,DCMain,MANDA,0000,0000,0000,,I... I... I'm sorry!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.98,0:15:06.47,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Even if it wasn't deliberate,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.47,0:15:11.15,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,you're still responsible \Nfor causing a murder.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.15,0:15:14.64,DCMain,KUMI,0000,0000,0000,,All I did was go and yell at her!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.83,0:15:17.30,DCMain,KAEDE,0000,0000,0000,,Mori-san, I have a request.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.30,0:15:21.27,DCMain,KAEDE,0000,0000,0000,,Please prove Kijima Kumi-san's innocence.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.49,0:15:22.56,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.96,0:15:24.15,DCMain,BOTH,0000,0000,0000,,Yashiro-kun.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.37,0:15:27.49,DCMain,KUMI,0000,0000,0000,,You believe me?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.49,0:15:29.53,DCMain,KAEDE,0000,0000,0000,,It's for Manda-san, actually.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.75,0:15:37.74,DCMain,KAEDE,0000,0000,0000,,If he caused the murder, then Manda-san \Nwill be held responsible, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.74,0:15:39.63,DCMain,KAEDE,0000,0000,0000,,I can't let that happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.63,0:15:43.03,DCMain,KAEDE,0000,0000,0000,,He's very important to \Nme. I owe him everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.74,0:15:46.17,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,You owe Manda-san everything?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.79,0:15:51.67,DCMain,KAEDE,0000,0000,0000,,I debuted as a broadcast \Nwriter with a radio drama.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.55,0:15:57.18,DCMain,KAEDE,0000,0000,0000,,He looked through the script I \Nbrought in as a total amateur.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.85,0:16:03.46,DCItalic,MANDA,0000,0000,0000,,Yashiro-chan, you're lucky \Nyou got to deal with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.33,0:16:10.33,DCMain,KAEDE,0000,0000,0000,,Manda-san, who was a director at the time,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.33,0:16:13.20,DCMain,KAEDE,0000,0000,0000,,took it upon myself to \Nput my show on the radio.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.20,0:16:16.04,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,So you owe him for helping you debut.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.39,0:16:21.29,DCMain,KAEDE,0000,0000,0000,,We never worked together after that,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.29,0:16:26.04,DCMain,KAEDE,0000,0000,0000,,but one month ago, he returned as \Nthe producer of the {\i1}Until Noon Show{\i0},
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.48,0:16:29.13,DCMain,KAEDE,0000,0000,0000,,and we were finally reunited.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.37,0:16:33.27,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,I see. You want to save \Nthe man who helped you.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.76,0:16:38.85,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,It's true that if she's innocent, then \NManda-san won't be held responsible.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.10,0:16:43.60,DCMain,MANDA,0000,0000,0000,,You gotta save me, Mori-chan!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.60,0:16:45.42,DCMain,MANDA,0000,0000,0000,,Mori-chan, please! Save me!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.42,0:16:49.73,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Inspector, does Kijima \NKumi-san have an alibi?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.91,0:16:52.80,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Every Friday she goes bar hopping.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.80,0:16:54.61,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,She said that's what she \Nwas doing last night.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.61,0:16:56.49,DCMain,KUMI,0000,0000,0000,,It's true!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.88,0:16:58.33,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.67,0:17:03.81,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Hello, this is Megure. Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.37,0:17:06.00,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,What? You found someone?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.32,0:17:12.88,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Got it. Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.14,0:17:17.19,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Kijima-san's alibi has been verified.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.19,0:17:18.26,DCMain,KUMI,0000,0000,0000,,See?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.63,0:17:25.34,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,An employee said she was drinking there last \Nnight from around 11 PM until past midnight.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.88,0:17:28.15,DCMain,MANDA,0000,0000,0000,,Which means...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.56,0:17:33.51,DCMain,KUMI,0000,0000,0000,,I told you I didn't kill her!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.19,0:17:42.84,DCMain,MANDA,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, what I did had absolutely \Nnothing at all to do with her murder.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.12,0:17:46.21,DCMain,KAEDE,0000,0000,0000,,That's great news, Manda-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.56,0:17:49.59,DCMain,MANDA,0000,0000,0000,,I've got the god of radio on my side.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.75,0:17:53.83,DCMain,KAEDE,0000,0000,0000,,But then who's the culprit?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.83,0:17:55.47,DCMain,MANDA,0000,0000,0000,,Who knows?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.97,0:18:02.51,DCMain,MANDA,0000,0000,0000,,In any case, now that we know our program \Nhad nothing to do with the case,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.51,0:18:05.41,DCMain,MANDA,0000,0000,0000,,we can get out of here.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.41,0:18:09.73,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Before that, Manda-san, \Nwhere were you last night?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.96,0:18:11.26,DCMain,MANDA,0000,0000,0000,,Me?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.26,0:18:14.01,DCMain,MANDA,0000,0000,0000,,I went drinking with these guys.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.01,0:18:18.25,DCMain,MANDA,0000,0000,0000,,But I suddenly felt tired, so \NI went home and went to bed.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.41,0:18:22.03,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, you were home alone?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.29,0:18:24.54,DCMain,MANDA,0000,0000,0000,,Wh-What about it?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.76,0:18:30.12,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,It's ironic, but now that our \Nprime suspect Kijima Kumi-san
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.12,0:18:32.01,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,has been proven innocent...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.01,0:18:34.92,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,We're forced to consider who stands
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.43,0:18:41.55,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,to benefit the most from the \Ndeath of Manda Towako-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.90,0:18:44.65,DCMain,INUYAMA,0000,0000,0000,,It's the end of the line, Manda-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.09,0:18:47.18,DCMain,INUYAMA,0000,0000,0000,,You killed your wife,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.48,0:18:51.16,DCMain,INUYAMA,0000,0000,0000,,and put that CD in Kijima \NKumi-san's mailbox
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.16,0:18:54.82,DCMain,INUYAMA,0000,0000,0000,,so it would look like she did it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.82,0:18:58.29,DCMain,INUYAMA,0000,0000,0000,,You made the police believe she had a motive.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.29,0:19:01.36,DCMain,MANDA,0000,0000,0000,,What are you talking about, Nino-chan?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.36,0:19:02.57,DCMain,KAEDE,0000,0000,0000,,Inuyama-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.84,0:19:08.08,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,We're also considering the possibility \NInuyama-san just mentioned.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.29,0:19:09.99,DCMain,KAEDE,0000,0000,0000,,But if that's true,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.99,0:19:13.59,DCMain,KAEDE,0000,0000,0000,,then wouldn't he have done something \Nto disprove Kijima-san's alibi?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.59,0:19:16.59,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Normally, yes, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.83,0:19:18.41,DCMain,KUJIRAI,0000,0000,0000,,It happened in the middle of the night.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.48,0:19:21.84,DCMain,KUJIRAI,0000,0000,0000,,He probably assumed she'd be unable
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.84,0:19:26.35,DCMain,KUJIRAI,0000,0000,0000,,to prove her alibi even \Nif he didn't do anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.18,0:19:29.61,DCMain,KUJIRAI,0000,0000,0000,,After all, Manda-san's all talk.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.61,0:19:31.85,DCMain,KAEDE,0000,0000,0000,,Kujirai-san, why?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.85,0:19:34.90,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,I've been wondering.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.90,0:19:39.63,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Do Inuyama-san and Kujirai-san \Nnot get along with Manda-san?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.63,0:19:42.36,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sure there's a lot going on between them.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.59,0:19:44.68,DCMain,INUYAMA,0000,0000,0000,,I know all about you, Manda-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.68,0:19:50.62,DCMain,INUYAMA,0000,0000,0000,,You're secretly scheming to prevent \Nme from becoming independent.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.62,0:19:54.31,DCMain,MANDA,0000,0000,0000,,Well, you know, the station has its reasons.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.31,0:19:56.29,DCMain,KUJIRAI,0000,0000,0000,,You don't love radio!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.66,0:19:58.00,DCMain,KUJIRAI,0000,0000,0000,,You never have.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.36,0:20:01.91,DCMain,KUJIRAI,0000,0000,0000,,You only think of your programs \Nas tools to make yourself rich.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.91,0:20:03.80,DCMain,KUJIRAI,0000,0000,0000,,You misappropriate them \Nfor your personal use!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.95,0:20:07.72,DCMain,MANDA,0000,0000,0000,,That has nothing to do with this.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.88,0:20:09.34,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,You're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.34,0:20:14.06,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Why don't you tell us all about it at the \Nstation where there won't be any outsiders?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.06,0:20:15.96,DCMain,MANDA,0000,0000,0000,,The station?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.97,0:20:21.83,DCMain,MANDA,0000,0000,0000,,I told you, last night I was \Nsound asleep at my home!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.83,0:20:23.32,DCMain,MANDA,0000,0000,0000,,You gotta believe me!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.57,0:20:26.82,Plan,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,He's been sent to hell!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.08,0:20:29.33,Plan,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,That damn bastard!!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.53,0:20:32.65,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,He has motive and no alibi,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.65,0:20:37.96,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,and it's true that he tried to have the \Nobnoxious woman living above her attack his wife.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.96,0:20:39.34,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.58,0:20:43.21,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't this a premeditated murder?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.21,0:20:47.47,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Could Manda-san really have come \Nup with this if he's all talk?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.70,0:20:51.30,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,He was just that desperate \Nto divorce his wife.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.96,0:20:52.98,DCMain,INUYAMA,0000,0000,0000,,Okada-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.17,0:20:55.04,DCMain,INUYAMA,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you for the other day.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.85,0:20:59.03,DCMain,KUJIRAI,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Abe. How did it go?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.56,0:21:00.90,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Yashiro-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.90,0:21:01.57,DCMain,KAEDE,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.78,0:21:05.95,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Those two seem to really hate Manda-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.18,0:21:07.04,DCMain,KAEDE,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.04,0:21:13.20,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Are you saying one of them did it \Nand is trying to frame Manda-san?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.40,0:21:16.21,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,I just thought it might be a possibility.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.16,0:21:18.46,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,You're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.81,0:21:27.70,DCMain,KAEDE,0000,0000,0000,,That's not possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.50,0:21:32.35,DCMain,KAEDE,0000,0000,0000,,It's true that they don't \Nget along with Manda-san,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.64,0:21:36.96,DCMain,KAEDE,0000,0000,0000,,but I can't believe they'd kill \Nhis wife just to get at Manda-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.96,0:21:40.23,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Right? See, you brat?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.46,0:21:43.41,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,But they hate him so much.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.83,0:21:47.32,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,I'm kind of hungry. \NI should get something to eat.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.32,0:21:49.82,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Listen to me!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.83,0:21:57.34,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Boy, I'm hungry.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.34,0:21:59.38,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Mister!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.59,0:22:07.38,Plan,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(1,1181)}Even if the boy suspects \Nsomething, it's too late
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.34,0:22:13.43,Plan,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(1,1350)}Everything has gone according to plan
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.60,0:22:18.15,DCMain,CULPRIT,0000,0000,0000,,It has ended in my victory!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.11,0:22:25.07,Plan,,0000,0000,0000,,To be continued
